  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "See:  https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/v0.11.1/specs/phase0/p2p-interface.md#whats-the-effect-of-empty-slots-on-the-sync-algorithm\r\n\r\nOur current sync algorithm can incorrectly disconnect peers who return only a subset of blocks requested.  We currently assume that all blocks requested are returned (we request our next batch of blocks [assuming it starts at the first slot after our previous request](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/caaa8095ad8b5d8b1a7dd27d927931048f425768/sync/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/teku/sync/PeerSync.java#L133)).  This means that if a peer only responds with a subset of requested blocks, our next batch of blocks will not connect to the previous batch, and we'll end up with an [UNKNOWN_PARENT error which we handle by disconnecting the peer](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/caaa8095ad8b5d8b1a7dd27d927931048f425768/sync/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/teku/sync/PeerSync.java#L146-L149).\r\n\r\n**Note**:  We can expect that honest peers will only omit blocks at then end of a range (for example, if the peer is under heavy load it may truncate its responses).  If blocks at the beginning or in the middle are omitted, the peer is misbehaving.",
